# <type>(<scope>): <subject> [EPIC-X-TX]
#
# Example: feat(api): add user authentication endpoint [EPIC-3-T2]
#
# Body (optional - explain WHY, not WHAT):
# - Key change 1
# - Key change 2
# - Why this change was needed
#
# Footer (optional):
# Refs: EPIC-X-TX
# Fixes #123
# BREAKING CHANGE: description of breaking change
#
# Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, chore
# Scopes: api, model, ui, docker, db, auth, tests, docs, deps
#
# Guidelines:
# - Use imperative mood: "add" not "added" or "adds"
# - Subject: lowercase, no period, max 72 chars (50 recommended)
# - Separate subject from body with blank line
# - Wrap body at 72 characters
# - Use body to explain what and why vs. how
#
# Good examples:
# feat(model): add ResNet50 image classification
# fix(docker): resolve h5py compilation on ARM64
# docs(readme): update setup instructions for Apple Silicon
# refactor(api): extract auth logic into separate service
#
# Bad examples:
# Fixed bug (no type/scope, past tense)
# Update code (vague, no context)
# WIP (not descriptive)
